DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: What can you tell me about the Garou?
DefaultChoiceDisplayText.LocalizedString: What can you tell me about the Garou?

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: Why are you interested in garou rituals?
DefaultChoiceDisplayText.LocalizedString: Why are you interested in garou rituals?

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: Don't perform the Ritual of Purification
DefaultChoiceDisplayText.LocalizedString: Don't perform the Ritual of Purification

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: What can you tell me about the Highlands?
DefaultChoiceDisplayText.LocalizedString: What can you tell me about the Highlands?

Message.SourceString: The animal within me, remembering a part of itself. And, for the first time in as long as I can remember, the beast does not stir.
Message.LocalizedString: The animal within me, remembering a part of itself. And, for the first time in as long as I can remember, the beast does not stir.

Message.SourceString: This shrine appears to be part of a garou ritual of some kind.
Message.LocalizedString: This shrine appears to be part of a garou ritual of some kind.

Message.SourceString: There's something beautiful about that, in a weird sort of way. Sheltering the shadow of monsters slain.
Message.LocalizedString: There's something beautiful about that, in a weird sort of way. Sheltering the shadow of monsters slain.

Message.SourceString: One in which the wild grows free and unhindered by the yoke of so called "civilisation".
Message.LocalizedString: One in which the wild grows free and unhindered by the yoke of so called "civilisation".

Message.SourceString: It has always been of interest to me, ever since my mother told me legends of such a place when I was a child.
Message.LocalizedString: It has always been of interest to me, ever since my mother told me legends of such a place when I was a child.

Message.SourceString: I believe the garou lived there once, before their goddess took them here.
Message.LocalizedString: I believe the garou lived there once, before their goddess took them here.

Message.SourceString: Where, might be better. It is the primordial forest, a world far far from ours.
Message.LocalizedString: Where, might be better. It is the primordial forest, a world far far from ours.

Message.SourceString: Aye, yes. an explanation. See, the garou weren't always on Ashenfall. They came from far, far away.
Message.LocalizedString: Aye, yes. an explanation. See, the garou weren't always on Ashenfall. They came from far, far away.

Message.SourceString: I believe the garou lived there once, before their goddess took them here.
Message.LocalizedString: I believe the garou lived there once, before their goddess took them here.

Message.SourceString: Hrmm, looks like you're carrying too much, young pup. Best lighten your load before I can give you this.
Message.LocalizedString: Hrmm, looks like you're carrying too much, young pup. Best lighten your load before I can give you this.

Message.SourceString: This shrine is dedicated to Lougrim, and looks like the place referred to in the Ritual of Purification. If you had the King's Token, 2 ram horns and 3 shock bulbs, you could perform the ritual here.
Message.LocalizedString: This shrine is dedicated to Lougrim, and looks like the place referred to in the Ritual of Purification. If you had the King's Token, 2 ram horns and 3 shock bulbs, you could perform the ritual here.

Message.SourceString: For a fraction of a moment the shrine is bathed in ethereal moonlight that shines from the ritual writing engraved on its surface. The King's Token seems different somehow, cleaner, lighter and somehow whole.
Message.LocalizedString: For a fraction of a moment the shrine is bathed in ethereal moonlight that shines from the ritual writing engraved on its surface. The King's Token seems different somehow, cleaner, lighter and somehow whole.

Message.SourceString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? Hrmm, some writing on a ritual? Let me take a look...
Message.LocalizedString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? Hrmm, some writing on a ritual? Let me take a look...

Message.SourceString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? Hrmm, you took a token from a garou king?
Message.LocalizedString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? Hrmm, you took a token from a garou king?

Message.SourceString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? No? Pity. Perhaps take a look through some of the garou camps?
Message.LocalizedString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? No? Pity. Perhaps take a look through some of the garou camps?

Message.SourceString: They make their homes in the spines of the dead wyrms around here, why not give them a look?.
Message.LocalizedString: They make their homes in the spines of the dead wyrms around here, why not give them a look?.

Message.SourceString: This... this is what I'm looking for. A ritual to take a piece of Antumnos, the primordial forest.
Message.LocalizedString: This... this is what I'm looking for. A ritual to take a piece of Antumnos, the primordial forest.

Message.SourceString: I... this is important to me, young pup. I ask that you keep looking. See if you can complete this ritual and bring me the token.
Message.LocalizedString: I... this is important to me, young pup. I ask that you keep looking. See if you can complete this ritual and bring me the token.

Message.SourceString: I'll explain everything once you do. .
Message.LocalizedString: I'll explain everything once you do. .

Message.SourceString: I'm impressed, that's no easy feat, that. Defeating a garou king.
Message.LocalizedString: I'm impressed, that's no easy feat, that. Defeating a garou king.

Message.SourceString: But this... is almost what I'm looking for. A piece of Antumnos, though it seems... sullied, somehow.
Message.LocalizedString: But this... is almost what I'm looking for. A piece of Antumnos, though it seems... sullied, somehow.

Message.SourceString: I need you to look around, see if there's anything you can do to purify it. To make it a pure piece of that long lost place.
Message.LocalizedString: I need you to look around, see if there's anything you can do to purify it. To make it a pure piece of that long lost place.

Message.SourceString: Ah, there it is. May I see it? The purified token?
Message.LocalizedString: Ah, there it is. May I see it? The purified token?

Message.SourceString: This shrine is dedicated to Lougrim, and looks like the place referred to in the Ritual of Purification. You have everything you need to perform the ritual.
Message.LocalizedString: This shrine is dedicated to Lougrim, and looks like the place referred to in the Ritual of Purification. You have everything you need to perform the ritual.

Message.SourceString: It's not quite right. It feels tainted, as if it's forgotten where it's from. Wait... that ritual you found, that's the answer!
Message.LocalizedString: It's not quite right. It feels tainted, as if it's forgotten where it's from. Wait... that ritual you found, that's the answer!

Message.SourceString: A ritual of purification, to turn this sullied trinket into a true piece of the Antumnos, the ancestral home.
Message.LocalizedString: A ritual of purification, to turn this sullied trinket into a true piece of the Antumnos, the ancestral home.

Message.SourceString: I... I need you to do this for me, young pup. Complete that ritual and purify the token. I'll explain everything on your return.
Message.LocalizedString: I... I need you to do this for me, young pup. Complete that ritual and purify the token. I'll explain everything on your return.

Message.SourceString: This... this trinket may seem like nothing to you. But for me it's an anchor to my ancestral home...
Message.LocalizedString: This... this trinket may seem like nothing to you. But for me it's an anchor to my ancestral home...

Message.SourceString: Sometime in the third age, I think, they were captured by Zamorakian forces and there they became part of a vampyre experiment, to create something new.
Message.LocalizedString: Sometime in the third age, I think, they were captured by Zamorakian forces and there they became part of a vampyre experiment, to create something new.

Message.SourceString: My ancesters... the werewolves. Aye, yes, my biggest secret. Tooth and claw beneath the silvery moon.
Message.LocalizedString: My ancesters... the werewolves. Aye, yes, my biggest secret. Tooth and claw beneath the silvery moon.

Message.SourceString: I left my people to try and hide from the beast, but it's always followed me... and been used against me.
Message.LocalizedString: I left my people to try and hide from the beast, but it's always followed me... and been used against me.

Message.SourceString: I don't want to hide any more. And this trinket will be a link to my ancestors, something to help me make peace with the beast.
Message.LocalizedString: I don't want to hide any more. And this trinket will be a link to my ancestors, something to help me make peace with the beast.

Message.SourceString: Here, something to show my gratitude for this piece of family history.
Message.LocalizedString: Here, something to show my gratitude for this piece of family history.

Message.SourceString: I have run from my wolf my entire life. Feared its fangs and claws. But, now, perhaps I can allow myself to face it.
Message.LocalizedString: I have run from my wolf my entire life. Feared its fangs and claws. But, now, perhaps I can allow myself to face it.

Message.SourceString: The animal within me, remembering a part of itself. And, for the first time in as long as I can remember, the beast does not stir.
Message.LocalizedString: The animal within me, remembering a part of itself. And, for the first time in as long as I can remember, the beast does not stir.

Message.SourceString: It is strange how a simple trinket can give you such a strong sense of connection. It feels like a piece of me pining for home.
Message.LocalizedString: It is strange how a simple trinket can give you such a strong sense of connection. It feels like a piece of me pining for home.

Message.SourceString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? Oh? You have the king's token? Let me see...
Message.LocalizedString: Found anything interesting yet, young pup? Oh? You have the king's token? Let me see...

Message.SourceString: They may seem brutal and savage, the garou, and frankly they are -- But there's a deeper spirituality to them as well.
Message.LocalizedString: They may seem brutal and savage, the garou, and frankly they are -- But there's a deeper spirituality to them as well.

Message.SourceString: Few places embody "survival of the fittest" quite like here.
Message.LocalizedString: Few places embody "survival of the fittest" quite like here.

Message.SourceString: My family has a history with the beastmen, dating back over the ages.
Message.LocalizedString: My family has a history with the beastmen, dating back over the ages.

Message.SourceString: I know, I know. What does a slayer master care about spirituality? But that's exactly the point, you see...
Message.LocalizedString: I know, I know. What does a slayer master care about spirituality? But that's exactly the point, you see...

Message.SourceString: Like we slayer masters, the garou are primal creatures. We understand the need to be hunter, not prey.
Message.LocalizedString: Like we slayer masters, the garou are primal creatures. We understand the need to be hunter, not prey.

Message.SourceString: The garou honour that truth, in every part of their culture. I find it... comforting.
Message.LocalizedString: The garou honour that truth, in every part of their culture. I find it... comforting.

Message.SourceString: The garou, the wildlife, even the very weather wants you dead. This place makes you face your mortality, lets you know you're alive.
Message.LocalizedString: The garou, the wildlife, even the very weather wants you dead. This place makes you face your mortality, lets you know you're alive.

Message.SourceString: The whole place is littered with the bones of great wyrms. Beasts so terrible I'm glad they're dead.
Message.LocalizedString: The whole place is littered with the bones of great wyrms. Beasts so terrible I'm glad they're dead.

Message.SourceString: Even I would think twice about trying to hunt one of those down. But here, the garou make their bones their home.
Message.LocalizedString: Even I would think twice about trying to hunt one of those down. But here, the garou make their bones their home.

Message.SourceString: It's a personal matter. An old family interest, shall we say?
Message.LocalizedString: It's a personal matter. An old family interest, shall we say?

Message.SourceString: They make their homes in the spines of the dead wyrms around here, why not give them a look?.
Message.LocalizedString: They make their homes in the spines of the dead wyrms around here, why not give them a look?.

Message.SourceString: I need you to look around, see if there's anything you can do to purify it. To make it a pure piece of that long lost place.
Message.LocalizedString: I need you to look around, see if there's anything you can do to purify it. To make it a pure piece of that long lost place.

Message.SourceString: I'll explain everything once you do. .
Message.LocalizedString: I'll explain everything once you do. .

Message.SourceString: I... I need you to do this for me, young pup. Complete that ritual and purify the token. I'll explain everything on your return.
Message.LocalizedString: I... I need you to do this for me, young pup. Complete that ritual and purify the token. I'll explain everything on your return.

Message.SourceString: My family has a history with the beastmen, dating back over the ages.
Message.LocalizedString: My family has a history with the beastmen, dating back over the ages.

Message.SourceString: Ah, yes, sorry, this won't mean anything to you. Pay an old fool no mind.
Message.LocalizedString: Ah, yes, sorry, this won't mean anything to you. Pay an old fool no mind.

Message.SourceString: There's something beautiful about that, in a weird sort of way. Sheltering the shadow of monsters slain.
Message.LocalizedString: There's something beautiful about that, in a weird sort of way. Sheltering the shadow of monsters slain.

Message.SourceString: You've come a long way, young pup, good to see. I'm here studying a race not seen for hundreds of years - the Garou.
Message.LocalizedString: You've come a long way, young pup, good to see. I'm here studying a race not seen for hundreds of years - the Garou.

Message.SourceString: I came here to uncover the truth. I heard tale of a ritual to preserve a fragment of a legacy my family has forgotten.
Message.LocalizedString: I came here to uncover the truth. I heard tale of a ritual to preserve a fragment of a legacy my family has forgotten.

Message.SourceString: I've been scouring garou camps, but I need your help and, well, a burden shared is a burden halved, eh?
Message.LocalizedString: I've been scouring garou camps, but I need your help and, well, a burden shared is a burden halved, eh?

Message.SourceString: They tend to camp beneath the spines of great wyrm remains. Scout those bones and let me know if you uncover anything.
Message.LocalizedString: They tend to camp beneath the spines of great wyrm remains. Scout those bones and let me know if you uncover anything.

Message.SourceString: This... this is what I've been looking for. A chance to own a piece of the Ancestral world.
Message.LocalizedString: This... this is what I've been looking for. A chance to own a piece of the Ancestral world.

Message.SourceString: Young pup, please, you must complete this ritual for me. I... I cannot say why, just yet, but it is important to me.
Message.LocalizedString: Young pup, please, you must complete this ritual for me. I... I cannot say why, just yet, but it is important to me.

Message.SourceString: Your journey begins with the death of the garou king. Go! Paint the earth with his blood. History favours the bold, and the bold carve their legend into the bones of the fallen.
Message.LocalizedString: Your journey begins with the death of the garou king. Go! Paint the earth with his blood. History favours the bold, and the bold carve their legend into the bones of the fallen.

Message.SourceString: No, you're right, I'm sorry to trouble you. Here, something to thank you for your effort.
Message.LocalizedString: No, you're right, I'm sorry to trouble you. Here, something to thank you for your effort.

Message.SourceString: What? You've uncovered a ritual text? Let me take a look at that.
Message.LocalizedString: What? You've uncovered a ritual text? Let me take a look at that.

Message.SourceString: This is a piece of the ancestral world of the garou, but it's been corrupted by this world and needs purification.
Message.LocalizedString: This is a piece of the ancestral world of the garou, but it's been corrupted by this world and needs purification.

Message.SourceString: I came here to uncover the truth. I heard tale of a ritual to preserve a fragment of a legacy my family has forgotten.
Message.LocalizedString: I came here to uncover the truth. I heard tale of a ritual to preserve a fragment of a legacy my family has forgotten.

Message.SourceString: Could you look into this? Check the garou camps, beneath the spines of great wyrm remains. Let me know if you uncover anything.
Message.LocalizedString: Could you look into this? Check the garou camps, beneath the spines of great wyrm remains. Let me know if you uncover anything.

Message.SourceString: Wait... that token. You've slain their king? May I see the token? Yes, yes, I thought so. This is almost what I'm looking for. Almost.
Message.LocalizedString: Wait... that token. You've slain their king? May I see the token? Yes, yes, I thought so. This is almost what I'm looking for. Almost.

Message.SourceString: Wait... that token. May I see it? The purified token?
Message.LocalizedString: Wait... that token. May I see it? The purified token?

Message.SourceString: You've come a long way, young pup, good to see. I'm here studying a race not seen for hundreds of years - the Garou.
Message.LocalizedString: You've come a long way, young pup, good to see. I'm here studying a race not seen for hundreds of years - the Garou.

Message.SourceString: The garou honour that truth, in every part of their culture. I find it... comforting.
Message.LocalizedString: The garou honour that truth, in every part of their culture. I find it... comforting.
